1.🚀 Kubernetes Services Project
📌 Overview

This project demonstrates different Kubernetes Service types used to expose and access applications:

ClusterIP – Internal communication within the cluster
NodePort – Access application using Node IP and port
LoadBalancer – Exposes application to external users (internet)

🧱 Technologies Used
Kubernetes
kubectl
YAML configuration files

1. ClusterIP (Default Service)
ClusterIP exposes the service only inside the Kubernetes cluster.
It cannot be accessed from outside the cluster.
==> working of clusterIP
Gives a virtual internal IP
Other Pods inside cluster can access it
External users cannot access it

2. NodePort
NodePort exposes the service on a specific port on every worker node.
==> WORKING
Opens a port (30000–32767)
Works on all nodes in cluster
Routes traffic to Pods

3. LoadBalancer
LoadBalancer exposes the service externally using a cloud provider’s load balancer.
==>WORKING
Creates an external IP automatically (AWS, Azure, GCP)
Routes traffic to Kubernetes service
Works like a real production entry point


